# UIScrollSystem

## Purpose
Scrolls the configured UI clip panel with the mouse wheel while the pointer is over it. Each frame, if a
MouseScrolledEventComponent is present and a UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent targets the scroll panel (or any
of its descendants), it accumulates the wheel delta into the panel's current UIClipComponent scroll
offset (clamped to the scrollable range) and emits a UIUpdateClipOffsetOneFrameComponent so the engine
applies it next frame. No-op when the config, the panel, or its UIClipComponent is absent, when there is
no scroll this frame, or when the pointer is not over the panel.

## Input Components
| Component | Access |
|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read |
| MouseScrolledEventComponent | read |
| UIOnHoverOneFrameComponent | read |
| BaseComponent | read |
| UIClipComponent | read |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| UIUpdateClipOffsetOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | New absolute scroll offset for the panel; applied by UIControlSystem |
